Tara Duncan

Aug 03, 2013 12:24 PM
Valid point, Chad Brodgesell. I hate to deviate from the bullshit theme, but it is a universal problem. Everyone loves a controversy, and everyone loves to judge and speculate without evidence or proof. Here, of all places, the focus should be on determining the facts, probing for details, and making informed decisions about the veracity of any claim. I have mentioned on occasion that this is not a dating site, nor should it be a forum to vent your prejudices or personal issues. There are very simple and basic ways to determine the facts in any situation which Scott demonstrates on a daily basis. Either you're a team of people working toward a common goal, or you're a bunch of folks in co-dependent relationships. You are all in a position to extract great value from some of the most erudite thinkers I have encountered in some time. How you choose to leverage that knowledge and information will determine your success in your ventures.

Tara Duncan

Aug 03, 2013 12:53 PM
Thanks for that. One final point before we devolve back into biological humour... There is still value to be had in the original post. Listen to the simple questioning methods, and the answers, taking into consideration that most people are not accustomed to holding up under even the most rudimentary questions, and there is a natural unease at being informed your conversation is recorded. In any situation where you want to establish facts you should be able to drill down to the basic information. If the person you are questioning is telling the truth they should be able to answer. If they are accomplished liars you have another issue altogether. Were the facts of the situation established? Does the chronology ring true? Do you have sufficient information to determine what actually transpired? Or are you being manipulated at the emotional level? That would be for you to decide.

i've said this before, TFL has been a huge psychology lesson for me first & foremost. When we look down through the page we can see whats wrong #1. FACTS dont change our minds. we are given a fact, the posts/questions that follow is "US/WE" attempting to rationalise those facts with our beliefs, in many cases the fact is contrary to our belief (cognitive dissonance) & so we end up externalising the Horseshit (we use this term as opposed to bullshit sometimes) .... all over the page . As regards the acknowledged barrier of stupidity/idiocy/language/locality... thats there for us all, so effort should be made to talk like you are talking to a fuckin tourist :p i have a beaten path outside my home where neighbours glare at me pacing up & down like a lunatic, thats all thats wrong with me, i cannot accept the facts & so i struggle, when my mind is capable of just realising facts for what they are everything else, EVERYTHING, will become easier... clearer...just procedural.until then I struggle, Its fair to say that if we were a little more internalised about our struggle, the threads would clean themselves.. maybe?
